t_desc: Seven noble families fight for control of the mythical land of Westeros. Friction between the houses leads to full-scale war. All while a very ancient evil awakens in the farthest north. Amidst the war, a neglected military order of misfits, the Night's W

sortedEpisodes.name: Winter Is Coming
sortedEpisodes.overview: Jon Arryn, the Hand of the King, is dead. King Robert Baratheon plans to ask his oldest friend, Eddard Stark, to take Jon's place. Across the sea, Viserys Targaryen plans to wed his sister to a nomadic warlord in exchange for an army.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Kingsroad
sortedEpisodes.overview: While Bran recovers from his fall, Ned takes only his daughters to Kings Landing. Jon Snow goes with his uncle Benjen to The Wall. Tyrion joins them.

sortedEpisodes.name: Lord Snow
sortedEpisodes.overview: Lord Stark and his daughters arrive at King's Landing to discover the intrigues of the king's realm.

sortedEpisodes.name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
sortedEpisodes.overview: Eddard investigates Jon Arryn's murder. Jon befriends Samwell Tarly, a coward who has come to join the Night's Watch.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Wolf and the Lion
sortedEpisodes.overview: Catelyn has captured Tyrion and plans to bring him to her sister, Lysa Arryn, at The Vale, to be tried for his, supposed, crimes against Bran. Robert plans to have Daenerys killed, but Eddard refuses to be a part of it and quits.

sortedEpisodes.name: A Golden Crown
sortedEpisodes.overview: While recovering from his battle with Jamie, Eddard is forced to run the kingdom while Robert goes hunting. Tyrion demands a trial by combat for his freedom. Viserys is losing his patience with Drogo.

sortedEpisodes.name: You Win or You Die
sortedEpisodes.overview: Robert has been injured while hunting and is dying. Jon and the others finally take their vows to the Night's Watch. A man, sent by Robert, is captured for trying to poison Daenerys. Furious, Drogo vows to attack the Seven Kingdoms.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Pointy End
sortedEpisodes.overview: Eddard and his men are betrayed and captured by the Lannisters. When word reaches Robb, he plans to go to war to rescue them. The White Walkers attack The Wall. Tyrion returns to his father with some new friends.

sortedEpisodes.name: Baelor
sortedEpisodes.overview: Robb goes to war against the Lannisters. Jon finds himself struggling on deciding if his place is with Robb or the Night's Watch. Drogo has fallen ill from a fresh battle wound. Daenerys is desperate to save him.

sortedEpisodes.name: Fire and Blood
sortedEpisodes.overview: With Ned dead, Robb vows to get revenge on the Lannisters. Jon must officially decide if his place is with Robb or the Night's Watch. Daenerys says her final goodbye to Drogo.

sortedEpisodes.name: The North Remembers
sortedEpisodes.overview: As Robb Stark and his northern army continue the war against the Lannisters, Tyrion arrives in King’s Landing to counsel Joffrey and temper the young king’s excesses.  On the island of Dragonstone, Stannis Baratheon plots an invasion to claim his late bro

sortedEpisodes.name: The Night Lands
sortedEpisodes.overview: In the wake of a bloody purge in the capital, Tyrion chastens Cersei for alienating the king’s subjects.  On the road north, Arya shares a secret with Gendry, a Night’s Watch recruit.  With supplies dwindling, one of Dany’s scouts returns with news of the

sortedEpisodes.name: What is Dead May Never Die
sortedEpisodes.overview: At the Red Keep, Tyrion plots three alliances through the promise of marriage.  Catelyn arrives in the Stormlands to forge an alliance of her own, but King Renly, his new wife Margaery, and her brother Loras Tyrell have other plans.  At Winterfell, Luwin

sortedEpisodes.name: Garden of Bones
sortedEpisodes.overview: Joffrey punishes Sansa for Robb’s victories, and Tyrion scrambles to temper the king’s cruelty. Catelyn entreats Stannis and Renly to unite against the Lannisters. Dany and her khalasar arrive at the prosperous city of Qarth. Tyrion coerces a relative int

sortedEpisodes.name: The Ghost of Harrenhal
sortedEpisodes.overview: The Baratheon rivalry ends, driving Catelyn to flee and Littlefinger to act. At King’s Landing, Tyrion’s source alerts him to Joffrey’s defense plan - and a mysterious secret weapon. Theon sails to the Stony Shore to prove he’s worthy to be called Ironbor

sortedEpisodes.name: The Old Gods and the New
sortedEpisodes.overview: Theon completes his master stroke. In King's Landing, the Lannisters send Myrcella off to be married. Arya comes face to face with a surprise visitor. Dany vows to take what is hers. Robb and Catelyn receive crucial news. Qhorin gives Jon a chance to prov

sortedEpisodes.name: A Man Without Honor
sortedEpisodes.overview: Jamie meets a distant relative. Daenerys receives an invitation to the House of the Undying. Theon leads a search party. Jon loses his way in the wilderness. Cersei counsels Sansa.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Prince of Winterfell
sortedEpisodes.overview: Theon receives a visitor. Arya asks her third and last death from Jaqen. While Stannis' army is reaching its destination, Davos is offered a reward.  Betrayal befalls Robb.

sortedEpisodes.name: Blackwater
sortedEpisodes.overview: Tyrion and the Lannisters fight for their lives as Stannis’ fleet assaults King’s Landing.

sortedEpisodes.name: Valar Morghulis
sortedEpisodes.overview: Tyrion awakens to a changed situation. King Joffrey doles out rewards to his subjects. As Theon stirs his men to action, Luwin offers some final advice. Brienne silences Jaime. Arya receives a gift from Jaqen. Dany goes to a strange place. Jon proves hims

sortedEpisodes.name: Valar Dohaeris
sortedEpisodes.overview: Jon meets the King-Beyond-the-Wall while his Night Watch Brothers flee south. In King's Landing, Tyrion wants a reward, Margaery shows her charitable nature, Cersei arranges a dinner party, and Littlefinger offers to help Sansa. Across the Narrow Sea, Dae

sortedEpisodes.name: Dark Wings, Dark Words
sortedEpisodes.overview: Sansa says too much. Shae asks Tyrion for a favor. Jaime finds a way to pass the time, while Arya encounters the Brotherhood Without Banners.

sortedEpisodes.name: Walk of Punishment
sortedEpisodes.overview: Tyrion shoulders new responsibilities. Jon is taken to the Fist of the First Men. Daenerys meets with the slavers. Jaime strikes a deal with his captors.

sortedEpisodes.name: And Now His Watch Is Ended
sortedEpisodes.overview: Trouble brews among the Night's Watch at Craster's. Margaery takes Joffrey out of his comfort zone. Arya meets the leader of the Brotherhood. Varys plots revenge on an old foe. Theon mournfully recalls his missteps. Daenerys deftly orchestrates her exit f

sortedEpisodes.name: Kissed by Fire
sortedEpisodes.overview: The Hound is judged by the gods. Jaime is judged by men. Jon proves himself. Robb is betrayed. Tyrion learns the cost of weddings.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Climb
sortedEpisodes.overview: Tywin plans strategic unions for the Lannisters. Melisandre pays a visit to the Riverlands. Robb weighs a compromise to repair his alliance with House Frey. Roose Bolton decides what to do with Jaime Lannister. Jon, Ygritte, and the Wildlings face a daunt

sortedEpisodes.name: The Bear and the Maiden Fair
sortedEpisodes.overview: Daenerys exchanges gifts with a slave lord outside of Yunkai. As Sansa frets about her prospects, Shae chafes at Tyrion’s new situation. Tywin counsels the king, and Melisandre reveals a secret to Gendry. Brienne faces a formidable foe in Harrenhal.

sortedEpisodes.name: Second Sons
sortedEpisodes.overview: King’s Landing hosts a wedding, and Tyrion and Sansa spend the night together. Daenerys meets the Titan’s Bastard. Davos demands proof from Melisandre. Sam and Gilly meet an older gentleman.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Rains of Castamere
sortedEpisodes.overview: Robb presents himself to Walder Frey, and Edmure meets his bride. Jon faces his harshest test yet. Bran discovers a new gift. Daario and Jorah debate how to take Yunkai. House Frey joins with House Tully.

sortedEpisodes.name: Mhysa
sortedEpisodes.overview: Joffrey challenges Tywin. Bran tells a ghost story. In Dragonstone, mercy comes from strange quarters. Daenerys waits to see if she is a conqueror or a liberator.

sortedEpisodes.name: Two Swords
sortedEpisodes.overview: Tyrion welcomes a guest to King’s Landing. At Castle Black, Jon Snow finds himself unwelcome. Dany is pointed to Meereen, the mother of all slave cities. Arya runs into an old friend.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Lion and the Rose
sortedEpisodes.overview: Tyrion lends Jaime a hand. Joffrey and Margaery host a breakfast. At Dragonstone, Stannis loses patience with Davos. Ramsay finds a purpose for his pet. North of the Wall, Bran sees where they must go.

sortedEpisodes.name: Breaker of Chains
sortedEpisodes.overview: Tyrion ponders his options. Tywin extends an olive branch. Sam realizes Castle Black isn’t safe, and Jon proposes a bold plan. The Hound teaches Arya the way things are. Dany chooses her champion.

sortedEpisodes.name: Oathkeeper
sortedEpisodes.overview: Dany balances justice and mercy. Jaime tasks Brienne with his honor. Jon secures volunteers while Bran, Jojen, Meera and Hodor stumble on shelter.

sortedEpisodes.name: First of His Name
sortedEpisodes.overview: Cersei and Tywin plan the Crown's next move; Dany discusses future plans; Jon Snow begins a new mission.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Laws of Gods and Men
sortedEpisodes.overview: Stannis and Davos set sail; Dany meets with supplicants; Tyrion faces down his father.

sortedEpisodes.name: Mockingbird
sortedEpisodes.overview: Tyrion gains an unlikely ally; Daario asks Dany to allow him to do what he does best; Jon's warnings about the vulnerability of the Wall are ignored; Brienne follows a new lead.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Mountain and the Viper
sortedEpisodes.overview: Unexpected visitors arrive in Mole's Town. Littlefinger's motives are questioned. Ramsay tries to prove himself to his father. Tyrion's fate is decided.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Watchers on the Wall
sortedEpisodes.overview: Jon Snow and the Night's Watch face a big challenge.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Children
sortedEpisodes.overview: Circumstances change after an unexpected arrival from north of the Wall. Dany must face harsh realities. Bran learns more about his destiny. Tyrion sees the truth about his situation.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Wars to Come
sortedEpisodes.overview: Cersei and Jaime adjust to a world without Tywin. Varys reveals a conspiracy to Tyrion. Dany faces a new threat to her rule. Jon is caught between two kings.

sortedEpisodes.name: The House of Black and White
sortedEpisodes.overview: Arya arrives in Braavos. Podrick and Brienne run into trouble on the road. Cersei fears for her daughter's safety in Dorne as Ellaria Sand seeks revenge for Oberyn's death. Stannis tempts Jon. An adviser tempts Daenerys.

sortedEpisodes.name: High Sparrow
sortedEpisodes.overview: In Braavos, Arya sees the Many-Faced God. In King's Landing, Queen Margaery enjoys her new husband. Tyrion and Varys walk the Long Bridge of Volantis.

sortedEpisodes.name: Sons of the Harpy
sortedEpisodes.overview: The Faith Militant grow increasingly aggressive. Jaime and Bronn head south. Ellaria and the Sand Snakes vow vengeance.

sortedEpisodes.name: Kill the Boy
sortedEpisodes.overview: Dany makes a difficult decision in Meereen. Jon recruits the help of an unexpected ally. Brienne searches for Sansa. Theon remains under Ramsay's control.

sortedEpisodes.name: Unbowed, Unbent, Unbroken
sortedEpisodes.overview: Arya trains. Jorah and Tyrion run into slavers. Trystane and Myrcella make plans. Jaime and Bronn reach their destination. The Sand Snakes attack.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Gift
sortedEpisodes.overview: Jon prepares for conflict. Sansa tries to talk to Theon. Brienne waits for a sign. Stannis remains stubborn. Jaime attempts to reconnect with family.

sortedEpisodes.name: Hardhome
sortedEpisodes.overview: Arya makes progress in her training. Sansa confronts an old friend. Cersei struggles. Jon travels.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Dance of Dragons
sortedEpisodes.overview: Stannis confronts a troubling decision. Jon returns to The Wall. Mace visits the Iron Bank. Arya encounters someone from her past. Dany reluctantly oversees a traditional celebration of athleticism.

sortedEpisodes.name: Mother's Mercy
sortedEpisodes.overview: Stannis marches. Dany is surrounded by strangers. Cersei seeks forgiveness. Jon is challenged.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Red Woman
sortedEpisodes.overview: The fate of Jon Snow is revealed. Daenerys meets a strong man. Cersei sees her daughter once again.

sortedEpisodes.name: Home
sortedEpisodes.overview: Bran trains with the Three-Eyed Raven. In King’s Landing, Jaime advises Tommen. Tyrion demands good news, but has to make his own. At Castle Black, the Night’s Watch stands behind Thorne. Ramsay Bolton proposes a plan, and Balon Greyjoy entertains other p

sortedEpisodes.name: Oathbreaker
sortedEpisodes.overview: Daenerys meets her future. Bran meets the past. Tommen confronts the High Sparrow. Arya trains to be No One. Varys finds an answer. Ramsay gets a gift.

sortedEpisodes.name: Book of the Stranger
sortedEpisodes.overview: Tyrion strikes a deal. Jorah and Daario undertake a difficult task. Jaime and Cersei try to improve their situation.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Door
sortedEpisodes.overview: Tyrion seeks a strange ally. Bran learns a great deal. Brienne goes on a mission. Arya is given a chance to prove herself.

sortedEpisodes.name: Blood of My Blood
sortedEpisodes.overview: An old foe comes back into the picture. Gilly meets Sam’s family. Arya faces a difficult choice. Jaime faces off against the High Sparrow.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Broken Man
sortedEpisodes.overview: The High Sparrow eyes another target. Jaime confronts a hero. Arya makes a plan. The North is reminded.

sortedEpisodes.name: No One
sortedEpisodes.overview: While Jaime weighs his options, Cersei answers a request. Tyrion's plans bear fruit. Arya faces a new test.

sortedEpisodes.name: Battle of the Bastards
sortedEpisodes.overview: As the Starks prepare to fight, Davos loses something dear. Ramsay plays a game. Daenerys faces a choice.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Winds of Winter
sortedEpisodes.overview: Tyrion counsels Daenerys on the upcoming campaign. Jon and Sansa discuss their future. Trials begin in King's Landing.

sortedEpisodes.name: Dragonstone
sortedEpisodes.overview: Jon organizes the defense of the North. Cersei tries to even the odds. Daenerys comes home.

sortedEpisodes.name: Stormborn
sortedEpisodes.overview: Daenerys receives an unexpected visitor. Jon faces a revolt. Tyrion plans the conquest of Westeros.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Queen's Justice
sortedEpisodes.overview: Daenerys holds court. Tyrion backchannels. Cersei returns a gift. Jaime learns from his mistakes.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Spoils of War
sortedEpisodes.overview: Daenerys fights back. Jaime faces an unexpected situation. Arya comes home.

sortedEpisodes.name: Eastwatch
sortedEpisodes.overview: Tyrion tries to find a way to make Daenerys listen to reason while Jon plans a dangerous new mission.

sortedEpisodes.name: Beyond the Wall
sortedEpisodes.overview: Jon and his team go beyond the wall to capture a wight. Daenerys has to make a tough decision.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Dragon and the Wolf
sortedEpisodes.overview: A meeting is held in King's Landing. Problems arise in the North.

sortedEpisodes.name: Winterfell
sortedEpisodes.overview: Arriving at Winterfell, Jon and Daenerys struggle to unite a divided North. Jon Snow gets some big news.

sortedEpisodes.name: A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms
sortedEpisodes.overview: The battle at Winterfell is approaching. Jaime is confronted with the consequences of the past. A tense interaction between Sansa and Daenerys follows.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Long Night
sortedEpisodes.overview: The Night King and his army have arrived at Winterfell and the great battle begins. Arya looks to prove her worth as a fighter.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Last of the Starks
sortedEpisodes.overview: In the wake of a costly victory, Jon and Daenerys look to the south as Tyrion eyes a compromise that could save countless lives.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Bells
sortedEpisodes.overview: Daenerys brings her forces to King's Landing.

sortedEpisodes.name: The Iron Throne
sortedEpisodes.overview: In the aftermath of the devastating attack on King's Landing, Daenerys must face the survivors.
